social_posts.post_text:
Family Traditions 
Don't have to be lofty or expensive 
Take a ton of planning or time-
.
One of our favorites
That we started when our boys were young,
Is to simply build a Fire
On a weekend day, 
And Gather round it to eat and chat
Sweet & Simple
.
Our children need our attention & our hearts
Not fancy toys or lavish gifts
But true connection, without distraction 
.
.
.
#sundaytraditions
#goplayoutside

It's not a stretch of the imagination 
To say that the last 18 months of life-
Have been the hardest, that I can remember-
.
For so many reasons,
That exist outside our family and our relationships with one another
.
Things like Fraud, Identity Theft,  Nightmare Biz contracts, that stretch for 2 years and simply won't end, 
A Negligent Bookkeeper and the ramifications of that, just to name a few....
.
But I decided long ago
That I would NEVER take the stance of-
Why is this "happening to ME"?
Iam not a victim, 
I have a choice how I view the landscape 
And things that are happening.
.
We operate together at a high frequency of load capacity
But when things come in rapid secession,
stretched out over months.
.
Forcing themselves, 
Onto an already "Life Filled Plate" 
When you feel full and don't want to eat anymore-
It's exhausting & a tad overwhelming-
.
So you pray Jesus makes your Life Plate,
Into a GIANT 💙 PLATTER
To accommodate the extra servings
.
.
.
#mamamusings

I think we grossly underestimate the power of our thoughts
The way we think in turn, affects whom we become-
Think......On.......That........
.
.
.
#thepowerofourthoughts

The past year has been full of much needed change, 
Albeit a tad scary & uncertain-
After doing things one way for a very long time-
.
But that way didn't serve me any longer
& at the time...it was all I knew 
.
Lessons I've learned in the past year
Movement can be for more❤️‍🔥 than shrinking our body
Food & True Nourishment can Heal
Minerals are like the Sparkplugs of our Body
Sometimes getting softer, can truly be better for you
.
I see the evidence of my changes in
My EYES
My Coloring
My Hair
My Curves
.
I simply wouldn't be where I am-
Without the guidance & shared knowledge of some amazing women- 
@korimeloy @wildlyonswellness @fallondanae @noellekovary @strong.sistas

Years ago when I started writing,
And purposely using the term
"Sacred Mundane"
Describing our days together ❤️ 
.
I was a Mama of much smaller Lyon's
Our days together seemed endless-
I was in the trenches & season of mothering
That are steeped in daily Pillars & Predictable rhythms
.
And now we find ourselves here
In the midst of beautiful & heartbreaking 
Wing stretching Blossoming & Change.
.
Our two oldest making short daily flights from the familiar Pillars
To establish their own❤️
.
But TODAY.....
We were all together again
And it was glorious 
.
We smooshed our faces together 
& captured the biggest pieces of my heart &
The Sacred Mundane 
Of this one beautiful life
& the people I love the most within it.
.
.
.
.
#sacredmundane

Forest Bathing
🌲🌲🌲🌲🌲

• Increase the quality of your sleep

• Improve your mood

• Increase your ability to find deep focus

• Boost your immune system

• Accelerate your recovery from illnesses and injury

• Reduce stress, and increase coping mechanisms for when it occurs

.
.
.
#forestbathing

Oh these two 💙🩵
Partners in Crime
Bunk Mates
Closest Counterparts
Squirrel and Pigeon 
The list goes on....
.
When I look at them together 
I feel the completeness they share
The strength of their relationship
And the vastness of their differences 
.
The way they've learned to honor each others preferences & ways
To lay the ground work for all the future relationships they will make
To respect & love someone, whom is different than you
.
To not force them to change & adjust 
To cheer on their strengths & gifts
To fall asleep nightly,
Three feet away from each other 
And your last words to be loving 
.
.
.
#valinandbohdi

I chose this
❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥
All the crazy & beautiful 
This one life can hold
.
Even with her gone home

.
To be fully immersed in their days
Looking for proof of life

.
Motherhood=Change

.

#mamamusings

Our days are filled with the sweet and the sour. 
Life played out amongst the roughness and the soft.
Finding solace in daily watching things unfold,
And the simple pleasure of filling our senses with them.
.
.

#sacredmundane

Over the weekend I felt called to clean out the recesses of my closet and the last of my- 
Pre Healing Journey clothes- 
.
I had held onto a stack of my favorite jeans & cords in my previous size (size 2) from the previous decade.
When I existed in a smaller body, then I do currently (size 10) 
.
I haven't looked at them with longing, more a simple NOTICING that they are there, and have been for the past two years, taking up space.....
.
See, I have no desire to go back to that size/shape/mindset/or quite frankly emotional capacity. 
I feel amazing in the space that I'm upholding. 
.
So I grabbed a stool, reached the high shelf & simply scooped them all into a box, bound for the Thrift shop. 
.
At first I didn't know, why I hadn't done it soone?
Then I thought- Actually I DO❤️‍🔥
.
It wasn't until NOW, that I felt ready to emotionally let go, and surrender even deeper to this journey.
.
Change is Change
It can feel scary 
It can feel exhilarating 
It's all in the lens in which we view it
.
.
.

Do you know the Calm feeling you get,
In your Mind & Body
When you've been out in Nature?
.
When we are in Nature, 
Our Body shifts into a Parasympathetic State, known as " Rest & Digest" mode vs "Fight or Flight" mode, which is triggered by stress & danger
.
We are continuing overloaded and overwhelmed 
In our daily modern living
Bombarded with the constant baraige of information 
.
Nature truly is one of the BEST, 
Nervous System regulators around-
And it's Free & Simple!
.
.
.
#Naturelover
#NervousSystemregulators

It truly has been one of the biggest blessings 
For all 4 of them, 
And us, as their parents-
.
To witness their growth & changes 
Played out on a sliver of land
The have Transformed, many times over.
.
Nothing but space, dirt, trees & imagination 
.
.
.
#goplayoutside

Just a couple of kids 🩵💙
Capturing the end of our Date Night 
They don't come around very often
But Boy, when they do-
The Mingling of Souls & Filling of Cups
.
Without family close
Minding 4 small boys, 
Was not for the faint of heart 
It felt like years & years went by
Without much mention of Date Nights
.
Seasons change
But some things remain the same🩵💙
.
.

We are the GATEKEEPERS
. 
The Sentry on Guard.
The Readers
The Watchers
The Listeners
The Doers
.
From the first flutter in my belly, their first breaking cry at birth and their first tentative steps...
Through it all, all the days-
That turn into years.
We DO NOT sleep on our watch,
Over them.
.
Mothering continues to be one of the most achingly beautifully transformative journey's-
One that I've been on, for 20 years
Though this road has taught me much, so far-
Iam in no way done yet,
.
I've learned their own unique language,
What their growing minds and bodies need-
As it's stoked my fires and confirmed the need
I have remained vigilant,
I will NOT abandon my post.
.
.
.
*This really needed a permanent place here
.
#wearethegatekeepers

Iam an Influencer-
.
I have four followers 
They are 18y 16y 14y 12y
& they are the loves of my life-
.
They aren't Influenced
By my Social Media or Stories
.
They are Influenced by
My Choices 
My Attitude 
My Words
My Priorities 
My Reactions
.
Who is following you?
.

What a treasure it is
To be the safe space, 
Amongst the tall grasses
For them to silently rest
.
We look forward 
To seeing the new ones, each year
.
.
.
#nevermowingourgrassagain

Did you know
Chaos provides and atmosphere

.

.

.
Here to Protecting their Peace

Mama's
Take all the pictures!
Capture them all, in a frame
.
And then purposely 
Recreate it, 10years-20years later
💙💙💙💙
.
Nothing marks the sweet passing of time
Quite like a Side by Side
.
.
.

It feels sudden
And not at all-
Like part of me
Has been preparing
For this moment 
Since they were born
A mark of growth & a
Passing of Time
.
.
.
#motheringteens

It feels almost like a 
"Rites of Passage"
When they reach the height
To open the window
& talk to me from the back deck
While I stand at the Kitchen sink
❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️
Its a funny thing,
How it holds more feelings 
With each & every passing son
❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️
Like a mark on the door frame
When you were tall enough
A snap shot capture
Of this moment

Things change yes,
Time passes-
Our relationship deepens
And lives transform
.
There is no hard lines
Only the ones we create
Between then & now
Past & Future
.
I refuse to stay in the Camp
Of "we only have our kids for 18 summers"
It actually makes me want to RAGE
.
That type of thinking is flawed & antiquated 
And quite frankly insights panic & fear
& unnecessary strain.....
.
Hear me when I say
WE HAVE TIME❤️
.
.
.

Almost 10" Difference 
But not in our Hearts🩵💙
Me & My Oldest 
.
18 years
Makes me want to 
Cling to Every Moment 
Imprinting it Forever 
.
.
#motheringteens 
#boymom

Our culture has never more, 
Engineered, manipulated & sucked all of the time freedom from childhood 
Than right now
.
Every living waking moment 
Is ear marked for 
Enhancement, accomplishing something or straight up being busy 
.
Childhood is short & sweet
I've guarded these precious years
From "FILLERS" that bring No Value
.
If they have no time
To think their OWN THOUGHT
Be Bored, Create Something ✨️ 
Work on Relationships 
Lay in the grass, soak up the sunshine, light a fire....
.
They NEED time, uninterrupted TIME
Free from Agenda 
This is a natural progression 
This is Maturing, it happens
Like it has for Centuries 
.

The older I get
The more I understand deeply 
The need to raise my voice
To advocate 
For the spaces in between 
Because let's be honest 
Life is lived in the journey 
None of us have arrived
And yet there is this Obsession 
With finding and maintaining Perfection 
 .
Not only is this chase fleeting...
It sucks all the Joy
Out of the Journey 
The messy middle
The small victories 
The cheer worthy moments
Of our every day, sacred lives
.
Here's to LIVING FULLY IN THE IN BETWEEN 
Not where we started 
But however long it takes✨️
Fully obsessed with our own journey 
.
.
.

Make Time Daily 
✨️✨️✨️✨️✨️✨️
To Decompress your days together 
To Look at each other, REALLY LOOK
To Converse.....about more than your Work & Kids
To give each other more than crumbs 
To Dream Together 
To find a reason to laugh
To remember why you fell in Love
To say I Love you 
.
Just a few things to hold on to
From a couple of kids, 
Who have loved each other for 25 years

Last night, we were invited to a longtime friend/acquaintance home. 
They are high powered Lawyer/Business Owners
.
With an only child, born of privilege 
Who is currently applying to all the best colleges. 
.
Our past engagements & conversations have always been filled with 
"Educating Politics Religion & Ideals"
.
Honesty, I tend to just endure our get togethers-
There are so few connections points
And the things they have found important or Debate worthy,
We simply don't see eye to eye on
.
And yet they desire to be with us....
To sit around the table & converse
.
Last night✨️felt Redemptive 
I felt incredibly proud of our 4 Sons
All glorious & unique in their own right 
.
I watched as they easily chatted & smiled
Helped with the BBQ, 
Washed dishes & cleaned up without being asked to
.
The husband touched my arm as we left
Glancing at his own son, 
Who had spent the evening on his phone...
.
Said to me,
I hope my son gains even 10% of what your boys emulate 
They are a Joy & a so Genuine 
And that's what this world needs
.
That's what we all need✨️

.

TO KEEP HOLDING THEM
.
And I really feel like they should
HOLD THE TEENAGERS✨️
.
Your relationship still matters the MOST!
Yes, above their peers, above everyone else
.

.

I made the decision 
Long ago....
To simply turn down the volume 
Of the narrative that claims
Everything must change terribly 
Once they become teenagers 
.
I refused to believe it
And set out to do the relational work
To counteract 
Everything that is spoken
Over & Over & Over
.
I loved my babies
All five of them ❤️💙💙💙💙
But man,
I LOVE my teens
Things just get better,
Richer, Deeper, Sweeter & More Complex 
.
Challenge the Narrative

This is something we practice 
In our family-
.
To not talk about Bodies, in conversation 
Yours or Others
There is 1 million other things, we can talk about
BODIES ARE NOT CONVERSATION MATERIAL 
.
Because how many times 
Have you heard, 
Or been apart of conversation that went like this-
.
Have you lost weight, 
You look amazing!?
Oh she's not looking her best
Maybe she let herself go
You've grown taller, taller than your brother now
You got your hair cut, why did you cut off your curls?
You look tired😵‍💫 are you okay...?
You've got your dads nose
You've got your mom's eyebrows
Wow, you have big feet!
.
These are examples of conversations we've been apart of, 
As people have just BLURTED THEIR OPINIONS onto us
.
If we all conversed about life giving things 
It would be a Hell of a lot better
Than this fodder
.

If I close my eyes✨️
I'm right back, at our beginning 
On that snowy Valentines day
.
As your tiny frame slipped,
Into my outstretched hands
As I crouched on our bathroom floor
.
You were sent,
Like a Balm, 
To heal my broken heart
.
My first son
There is something 
About all we've been through together 
That has laid the most solid foundation 
For our mutual admiration ✨️
You are my Dearheart 
.

Dad's-

In a good-natured "Speed Saw Competition"
They were all smiles and laughs
.

We've never encouraged them,
To complete against each other
